import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['x'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['x'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['diff'] = data['x'] - data['y']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['diff'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['diff'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['diff'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="x", y="y", data=data)
    corr = data['x'].corr(data['y'])
    ax.axhline(y=data['y'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='y mean')
    ax.axvline(x=data['x'].mean(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='x mean')
    ax.axhline(y=data['y'].median(), color='b', linestyle='--', label='y median')
    ax.axvline(x=data['x'].median(), color='m', linestyle='--', label='x median')
    ax.axhline(y=data['y'].min(), color='c', linestyle='--', label='y min')
    ax.axvline(x=data['x'].min(), color='y', linestyle='--', label='x min')
    ax.axhline(y=data['y'].max(), color='k', linestyle='--', label='y max')
    ax.axvline(x=data['x'].max(), color='orange', linestyle='--', label='x max')
    ax.axhline(y=corr, color='purple', linestyle='--', label='correlation')
    ax.legend(loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
